cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the task of generating images from text descriptions, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep architecture and GAN formulation, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of recurrent neural networks for text feature representation, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also involves the use of GANs for image generation, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
